The upgrade task UpgradeTask2710DropUnusedColumnsFromBrs can fail if the constraint being dropped doesn't exist.
I've actually seen several customers with missing constraints, this generally happens when they have DB corruption and we add a table/column at at later stage, then try to add constraints.

Official workaround for MySQL:
{code}
alter table USER_COMMIT add constraint FKF8936C2BA958B29F foreign key (BUILDRESULTSUMMARY_ID) references BUILDRESULTSUMMARY (BUILDRESULTSUMMARY_ID);
{code}

Simply add an icon to your project and add the following inside the taskType elements
{code}
