Add a public component named (just a suggestion) {{CurrentRequest}} that will provide current user, locale and all other important stuff associated with currently executing web request without requiring to provide any parameters. e.g.:

{code}
User getCurrentUser();

Locale getLocale();

I18nBean getI18n();
{code}

etc. See e.g. {{JiraAutheticationContext}} in JIRA. This would make it convenient for both core bamboo code and plugins to retrieve this data without having to know the gory details of retrieving this stuff from various other components (like {{ActionContext}} etc.)

When no repository was created, the Add Repository button allignment is weird. 

The following CSS causes it to float around by 5% from the left.

{code}
.no-repository > #repository-list > .aui-toolbar {
left: -40px;
margin-left: 5%;
}

#repository-list > .aui-toolbar {
margin: 0 5px 1em;
vertical-align: middle;
}
{code}

We should get rid of the first block completely and remove the 5px in the second block to left-align it with the text.
